# Regenerable live renders (run: vitest --config tools/design-parity/vitest.config.mjs)
surfaces/*/live/

# Regenerable measurement artifacts.
#
# These are OUTPUTS of the pipeline, not inputs: `extract-playwright.mjs` writes
# the design-/live- computed-style profiles from anchors.json, and compare.mjs
# writes report-*.json alongside its markdown twin. Re-running the harness
# reproduces them byte-for-byte, so versioning them adds hundreds of noisy files
# that no one reads and that conflict on every re-measure.
#
# What IS tracked, deliberately:
#   anchors.json          hand-authored design<->live map — the real input
#   *.md (report/FINDINGS/AUDIT)  the human-readable findings
#   lib/render-live-*.test.tsx    hand-written harnesses that produce the live side
# Trade-off to know: without the JSON you cannot diff two runs without
# re-rendering both sides. That is cheap (one vitest run + the extractor), which
# is why regeneration wins over version control here.
surfaces/*/out/design-*.json
surfaces/*/out/live-*.json
surfaces/*/out/report*.json

# Throwaway probe/driver scripts.
#
# These MUST be written inside the repo tree: node resolves `playwright` by
# walking UP to the root node_modules, so a scratch script in /tmp cannot import
# it. That makes stray scratch files a standing risk of being committed, so the
# convention is a name/dir the repo ignores by default:
#   *.tmp.mjs      one-off checks next to whatever they are checking
#   scratch/       anything larger
#   probe*.mjs     ad-hoc "what does this state actually render" probes
# The durable harness lives in lib/ and is tracked; if a probe is worth keeping,
# promote it into lib/ with a real name instead of un-ignoring it here.
*.tmp.mjs
scratch/
probe*.mjs

# Stronger version of the same rule: a surface directory holds DATA (anchors,
# reports, vendored design source) — never executable scripts. Durable tooling
# belongs in lib/, where it is reviewed, reused and named. Anything an agent
# leaves behind under surfaces/ is by definition a one-off.
surfaces/**/*.mjs
